to be on a brand-new, unapologetically automated small SUV with front and rear cameras, flick a toggle to ‘B’ for ‘Brake’ when pulling in to a parking slot, and just let the car do its thing as you walk.

Better still if the car is the 2018 Jaguar E-Pace, SUV-lite: this gourmand of engines. A pleasingly puny ‘entry-level’ 2.0litre, 4-cylinder belt-missile makes 147kW, good enough for zero to 100km/h in 7.5s and a top speed of 210km/h.

Launch control for the $79,900 “entry-level” E-Pace D150 FWD (the petrol model tops out from $93,866) reduced shift-change induced wrist-pulses to a minimum, while the Full-time AWD 2.0litre D180 adds a beautiful diesel rumble of 132kW and up the tech-on-board stakes.

Luxor sheet metal – with a trapezoidal vented snout and a short yawning nose – are the aesthetic motifs of this cat-still-in-the-bag, coming tastefully close to rivals like the 3 Series on the outside, while mix-and-matching the cabin materials and colours of more sporty Evoque and more senior Jaguar models.
